data.name: rulesText.Text
data.value:
Air Commander is a turn based game where you try to take down your opponent's fighter jet by guessing where it is located on a 10x10 grid. Each players takes a turn and calls out where on the grid they wish to strike (ex. G6) followed by the game stating if it was a hit, miss, kill or a wreckage.
Hits - means you hit part of the plane but not the cockpit Miss - the player missed the plane entirelly Kill - the cockpit was hit, which destroyed the plane and is now considered a wreckage Wreckage - the player hit a plane that already had its cockpit destroyed
Each player gets to place 2 fighter jets on their respective grids( the planes cannot overlap each other nor can they clip outside their 10x10 grid), only when one player looses all their planes by getting their cockpits destroyed does the game end.
